ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I look forward to becoming a parent with confidence in my role as a parent.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I feel I can catch on quickly to the basic skills of caring for my child.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I think I will have difficulty interpreting my baby's cries, knowing whether he or she wants to be fed rather than played with or held.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I imagine myself getting uptight if my baby becomes fussy or irritable for longer than a few minutes.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I expect to be comfortable playing actively with my baby and getting him or her to smile at me.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I feel unprepared in becoming a parent.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I imagine myself in most circumstances, even when I am tired, able to cope well with meeting my baby's needs.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: Touching, holding, and being affectionate with my baby will be comfortable and pleasurable for me.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I think I will be able to trust my feelings and intuitions about taking care of my baby.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I wonder if I really can understand my baby's needs.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I am unsure just how much attention I should give my baby.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I expect to be able to soothe my baby easily when he or she is crying or fussing.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I am concerned that my patience with my baby may be limited.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me

ElementDescription: I expect to feel comfortable and natural using baby-talk.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: I find nothing unusually complicated or difficult about the prospect of feeding, playing with, or providing day-to-day care for a child.
Notes: 1 = Not at all representative of me; 3 = Slightly representative of me; 5 = Moderately representative of me; 7 = Strongly representative of me

ElementDescription: The thought of being solely responsible for my child is frightening.
Notes: 1 = Strongly representative of me; 3 = Moderately representative of me; 5 = Slightly representative of me; 7 = Not at all representative of me
